summary:
The Security Council, recalling previous resolutions on Sudan, stresses its commitment to peace in Sudan, including through the Abuja Talks and implementation of the Comprehensive Peace Agreement. The Council urges parties to reach a peace agreement, and recalls the midterm briefing of the Panel of Experts. 

The Council, determining the situation in Sudan remains a threat to international peace and security, decides to:

1. Extend the mandate of the Panel of Experts until 29 March 2006;
2. Request the Panel to report on implementation of measures imposed by previous resolutions, through the Committee established by resolution 1591 (2005);

The Council decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
